THE SECULAR POEM.

Tms poem, designed to be sung at the celebration of the Secu- lar Games‚ by a choir of fifty-four boys and girIS, an equal number of each, is considered one of the most finished performances -of antiquity. These games were celebrated once in an age, or about a hundred years. They were instituted in consequence of certain prophecies contained in the Sibylline Books, This cele- bration was originally distinguished by three solemn festivals, which were afterwards united in one festival, which continued three days and three nights successively. The first celebration of the Secu- lar Games was in the year of Rome 2453 the second was in 3053 the. third was in 505; the fourth was in 6053 and the fisth, for which Horace wrote this poem, was in 737.
